# 🌿 **English Reflection**

The comments shared today beautifully complete one another.

Swami Ashokanand Ji reminds us that **reason (*yukti*) is not the destination—it is the bridge.**

Without reason,

faith may remain fragile.

Without faith,

reason may become dry.

Together,

they lead to direct realization.

Shri Gulshan Madan Ji then carries us beyond reasoning.

He reminds us that the Self is already **Existence, Consciousness, Peace, and Bliss.**

Bondage does not belong to the Self.

It belongs to the mistaken identification of the mind.

His image of the spider is especially striking.

Just as the spider spins its own web,

the mind spins a web of thoughts,

attachments,

and fears—

then imagines itself trapped within them.

Self-realization is not the destruction of the Self,

nor the creation of freedom.

It is the recognition that the Witness was never caught in the web.

This is the timeless message of Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha.

